The paper presents a new methodology that combines neural networks with the Theory of Connections (ToC) to estimate the solutions of partial differential equations (PDEs). This methodology has two major advantages over other popular methods used to estimate the solutions of PDEs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Systems and Control), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
